Lovejoy, 1996 ); ( 4 ) angular cartilages present; a single cartilage in all of our examined material of Plesiotrygon , and usually two in Potamotrygon (absent in remaining myliobatiforms including Heliotrygon and Paratrygon ; for general discussion on angular cartilages, see
Carvalho et al., 2004 ); ( 5 ) strong hyomandibular- Meckelian ligament (however, this feature may be plesiomorphic at this level; this character was extensively discussed in
